---
import ProjectLayout from '../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro';
---
<ProjectLayout
  title="Israel Train Stations Dashboard"
  year="2025"
  section="Data Science & Analysis"
  category="Interactive Dashboard · Streamlit"
  tools={['Python', 'Streamlit', 'Pandas', 'Plotly', 'Folium', 'GTFS']}
>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Objective</h2>
    <ul class="proj-list">
      <li>Israel Railways publishes detailed open data on station activity, but exploring it station-by-station and period-by-period takes real digging.</li>
      <li>This project turns that raw open data into an interactive dashboard that lets anyone — planners, researchers or just curious commuters — explore <strong>passenger departure patterns</strong> across Israel's train stations without writing a line of code.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">What It Does, in General Terms</h2>
    <ul class="proj-list">
      <li><strong>Data:</strong> Combines official departure activity data from the Israeli Government Open Data Portal with GTFS station coordinates and schedules, focused on the 2025 service year.</li>
      <li><strong>Station explorer:</strong> Pick any station from the network and view its departure activity at day, month or year resolution — including average daily departures over custom date ranges.</li>
      <li><strong>Working-day logic:</strong> Automatically separates regular service days from weekends and Israeli public holidays (using the Jewish calendar), so comparisons reflect real operating patterns rather than being skewed by non-service days.</li>
      <li><strong>Time-of-day breakdown:</strong> Shows how a station's departures are distributed across seven service periods of the day, as a share of its yearly total — useful for spotting peak-hour load and off-peak gaps.</li>
      <li><strong>Map view:</strong> An embedded interactive Folium map places every station in its geographic context alongside its activity figures.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Try It / Code</h2>
    <p class="proj-body">
      The dashboard is deployed live on Streamlit Community Cloud, and the full source is on GitHub.
    </p>
    <div class="proj-links">
      <a class="proj-external proj-external-primary" href="https://israeltrainstationsproject.streamlit.app/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        Open live dashboard →
      </a>
      <a class="proj-external" href="https://github.com/ofer-geo/israel_train_stations_project" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        View repository on GitHub →
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</ProjectLayout>

<style>
  :global(.proj-list) {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
    max-width: 68ch;
  }
  :global(.proj-list li) {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #2A2A2A;
    padding-left: 1.2em;
    position: relative;
  }
  :global(.proj-list li::before) {
    content: '—';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: #3D5E35;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .proj-links {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-top: 12px;
  }
  .proj-external {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #3D5E35;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .proj-external:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  .proj-external-primary {
    padding: 10px 20px;
    color: #F0EAE0;
    background: #3D5E35;
    border-radius: 4px;
    transition: background 0.15s;
  }
  .proj-external-primary:hover { background: #2E4828; text-decoration: none; }
</style>
